"title": "8776: lies",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8776: lies",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Statements or answers which are untrue. Lying, false witness, deceit and false dealings are all condemned in Scripture.</p>\n<h2>Lying is condemned</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:12-Ps34:13\">PSA 34:12–34:13</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:25\">EPH 4:25</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:9-Col3:10\">COL 3:9–3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:16\">EXO 20:16</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:20\">DEU 5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:11-Lev19:12\">LEV 19:11–19:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:16-Prov6:17\">PRO 6:16–6:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:22\">PRO 12:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:9-Jer17:10\">JER 17:9–17:10</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of lying</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:4-Gen3:5\">GEN 3:4–3:5</a> <em>the serpent to Eve</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:9\">GEN 4:9</a> <em>Cain to the LORD</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:11-Gen12:13\">GEN 12:11–12:13</a> <em>Abraham urges Sarah to lie to the Egyptians</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:15\">GEN 18:15</a> <em>Sarah to the LORD</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:1-Gen20:2\">GEN 20:1–20:2</a> <em>Abraham to Abimelech</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:6-Gen26:7\">GEN 26:6–26:7</a> <em>Isaac to the men of Gerar</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:18-Gen27:19\">GEN 27:18–27:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:24\">GEN 27:24</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:14-Gen39:18\">GEN 39:14–39:18</a> <em>Potiphar's wife to her household servants</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:22-2Kgs5:27\">2KI 5:22–5:27</a> <em>Gehazi to Naaman and then to Elisha</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:1-Acts5:10\">ACT 5:1–5:10</a> <em>Ananias and Sapphira</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:11\">ACT 6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:13\">ACT 6:13</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts25:7\">ACT 25:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:8\">ROM 3:8</a></p>\n<h2>Lying will not go unnoticed or unpunished</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:9\">PRO 19:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:6\">PSA 5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps52:2-Ps52:5\">PSA 52:2–52:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:23\">PSA 55:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps101:7\">PSA 101:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:13-Jer6:15\">JER 6:13–6:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:32\">JER 23:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:1\">NAM 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:9-1Tim1:10\">1TI 1:9–1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:8\">REV 21:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:27\">REV 21:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:15\">REV 22:15</a></p>\n<h2>God's people should resist the temptation to lie</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job27:2-Job27:5\">JOB 27:2–27:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:2\">REV 2:2</a></p>\n<h2>Lying can be an act of malice</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:24-Prov26:28\">PRO 26:24–26:28</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Lying can be the sign of a dead conscience</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:1-1Tim4:2\">1TI 4:1–4:2</a></strong></p>\n<h2>A lying spirit</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:21-1Kgs22:23\">1KI 22:21–22:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:20-2Chr18:22\">2CH 18:20–18:22</a></p>\n<h2>Lying is the hallmark of the devil and the antichrist</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:44\">JHN 8:44</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:22\">1JN 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:14\">REV 13:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:7-Rev20:10\">REV 20:7–20:10</a></p>",
